4
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:16,380
So last year we did the Summer of Math Exposition number 1

5
00:00:16,380 --> 00:00:21,440
Which was essentially an open invitation for people to make explanatory math content

6
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:23,520
That they might have thought about making before

7
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:27,020
But just get an excuse for us to all do it at the same time and together

8
00:00:27,020 --> 00:00:29,760
The way we did it is we framed it as a contest

9
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:34,180
